  [Text] Macao, April 8 (XINHUA) -- Macao Governor General 
Vasco Joaquim Rocha Vieira said that the forthcoming visit of 
Portuguese Premier Cavaco Silva to China would not only 
consolidate the friendly relations between the two governments 
of Portugal and China, but would also further strengthen such 
friendly relations of the two sides. 
  He made his remarks when leaving Macao this evening for 
Lisbon, for the purpose to accompany Portuguese Premier Cavaco 
Silva's visit to China. 
  He said "I think that the efforts made by the two 
governments 
in strengthening their friendship and mutual trust will be 
beneficial to Macao." 
  He continued, Macao is now in the transitional period, 
noting 
